fertile, and rice paddies are the dominant agricultural feature of the island. in some areas, paddies take the form of dramatic sculpted terraces which efficiently utilise every available acre of land for cultivation. especially beautiful examples of terraced paddies can be found in the centre of the island north of ubud and in east bali around tirta gangga. elsewhere, gently rolling rice fields make for very pleasing rural scenery. rice paddies in east bali with mount agung in the background all of bali's mountains are volcanoes, some long dormant and some still active. at 3,142 metres (10,308 ft), magnificent mount 